-- Northam Platinum Says It Resumed Pay Talks With Union in Bid to End Strike
-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 2010-10-11T07:40:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/northam-platinum-says-it-resumed-pay-talks-with-union-in-bid-to-end-strike.html
Northam Platinum Ltd. resumed talks
with workers over pay today, Ecliff Tantsi, a spokesman for
South Africa’s National Union of Mineworkers, said by mobile
phone.  Workers went on strike on Sept. 5 over a disagreement over
pay increases, shutting the company’s only mine.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Carli Lourens at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net  